Package mmj.pa

Class ProofAsstPreferences

java.lang.Object
mmj.pa.ProofAsstPreferences
public class ProofAsstPreferences extends Object
Holds user settings/preferences used by the Proof Assistant.

    • defaultFileNameSuffix

      public Setting<String> defaultFileNameSuffix
      Default file name suffix, such as ".txt" or ".mmp".

    • fontSize

      public Setting<Integer> fontSize
      Font size used in ProofAsstGUI.

      NOTE: presently, font size is set in ProofAsstBoss as part of the start-up of ProofAsstGUI, based on a RunParm. Then during operation of ProofAsstGUI the user can increase or decrease the font size used, and those settings propagate to these ProofAsstPreferences (but are not stored externally for use in the next session -- permanent setting should be made in the RunParm file.)

    • fontFamily

      public Setting<String> fontFamily
      Font Family Name used in ProofAsstGUI.

      Note: Proof Assistant formatting of formulas (via TMFF) REQUIRES a fixed-width font for symbol alignment! A proportional or variable-width font can be used but symbol alignments may be off.

      Note: The default is "Monospaced", which works just fine...

      public Setting<Boolean> recheckProofAsstUsingProofVerifier
      On/off indicator instructing Proof Assistant to double-check every proof steps generated proof tree using the Proof Engine (VerifyProofs).

    • exportFormatUnified

      public Setting<Boolean> exportFormatUnified
      On/off indicator instructing the Proof Assistant Export to use unified or "un-unified" format for exported proofs.

      Note: this applies to exported proofs written via ProofAsst.exportToFile, which is triggered via BatchMMJ2 "RunParm ProofAsstExportToFile" as well as the "ProofAsstBatchTest" (the latter when no input file is specified and an "export to memory" is implicitly requested.)

    • exportHypsOrder

      public Setting<HypsOrder> exportHypsOrder
      Set the order in which the Proof Assistant Export should output proof step logical hypotheses (a testing feature for Proof Assistant.)

      Note: this applies to exported proofs written via ProofAsst.exportToFile, which is triggered via BatchMMJ2 "RunParm ProofAsstExportToFile" as well as the "ProofAsstBatchTest" (the latter when no input file is specified and an "export to memory" is implicitly requested.)

    • exportDeriveFormulas

      public Setting<Boolean> exportDeriveFormulas
      On/off indicator instructing the Proof Assistant Export to output blank formulas -- or not -- for non-qed derivation steps (not logical hyps).

      Note: this applies to exported proofs written via ProofAsst.exportToFile, which is triggered via BatchMMJ2 "RunParm ProofAsstExportToFile" as well as the "ProofAsstBatchTest" (the latter when no input file is specified and an "export to memory" is implicitly requested.)

    • importCompareDJs

      public Setting<Boolean> importCompareDJs
      On/off indicator instructing the Proof Assistant Batch Test Import to compare generated Dj Vars with the originals.

    • importUpdateDJs

      public Setting<Boolean> importUpdateDJs
      On/off indicator instructing the Proof Assistant Batch Test Import to update the originals that are stored in memory (does not update the .mm file though.)

    • unifySearchExclude

      public Setting<Set<String>> unifySearchExclude
      Array of assertions that will be excluded from the proof unification search process.

      This feature is primarily needed for redundant theorems that are carried in a Metamath database because they have a different proof (other possibilities exist.)

    • excludeDiscouraged

      public Setting<Boolean> excludeDiscouraged
